    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a91eb63_d15ab2f8",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbHostListener.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 101,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-21T19:43:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m confused: onHostServerConnection was called. This implies that we were listening for connections from the host server _and_ that host server connected to us on the port we were listening on |mServer-\u003eport()|.\n\nIf mActiveGuest-\u003eonHostConnection succeeded (The else case starting line 98) , it means that an end to end channel has been setup. Why are we notifying the host server of the same port that it just created a connection on?\n\nOTOH, if mActiveGuest-\u003eonHostConnection failed, we deleted the active guest, and we need the host server to try to connect again. In that case, it might be beneficial to once again tell it that we\u0027re listening for connections on |mServer-\u003eport|.\n\nbtw, in the success case, we might want to stop listening on mServer if there are no more guests pending that can be connected, and then restart in addGuest when we find an empty list of guests.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 99,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 101,
        "endChar": 9
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8a91eb63_46f44aed",
        "filename": "android/emulation/AdbHostListener.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 55,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-07-21T19:43:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Orthogonal idea: We could use a TLS variable to mark the \"thread type\" (qt main loop, qemu main loop, render thread, vcpu thread).\nThen, provide a method that compiles to an assert that you are in the right kind of thread in the debug build (and to a noop in non-debug build).\n\nWe could pepper the code with this assert to state such assumptions then.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 55,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 55,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "370d177b71d3cf2ea602fee88060406172e94709",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
